<p><span class="subtitle">About Citizen Services:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>The Citizens Service Center was created in 1996 to provide Stamford residents with a single telephone number for service and information requests.</p>
<p>The mission of the Citizenâ€™s Service Center is to provide a convenient and effective mechanism for receiving and responding to complaints, services and information requests for residents and visitors to Stamford so that requests and complaints are resolved with speed, fairness and courtesy.&nbsp;</p>
<p>You can <a href="?navid=762">request services online</a> or by calling the Citizens Service Center during business hours.</p>
<p>
For after hours assistance please call the Non-Emergency Police Dispatch at (203) 977-4444.
